          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                                        <date>3 decr. 5613—1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Revd Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Tho' our friendship has been dissolved from
                                        causes<lb/> at present unnecessary to be recapitulated, yet
                                        confident that where<lb/> honor and justice are invoked, you
                                        will be found to be the<lb/> last to be swayed by prejudice
                                        or party feeling, I address you.<lb/> I am a Candidate for
                                        the still vacant office in <placeName>Savannah,
                                                  Ga.</placeName><lb/> (the <persName>Revd. Mr
                                                  Rosenfeld</persName> having declined the same, as
                                        I learn by a<lb/> letter therefrom this day). Had my
                                        application been forwarded<lb/> with the others from
                                                  <placeName>Sava.</placeName> To <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName> &amp;
                                                  <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
                                        <persName>Dr. De La Motta</persName><lb/> would have been
                                        enabled (as he says in his letter) to have made<lb/>
                                        personal enquiries. Now it behooves me to address those
                                        who<lb/> know me. Having stated in my application that I
                                        am<lb/> unfortunately <add>Hebrew</add> and having mentioned
                                        your name in<lb/> conjunction with that of <persName>A. Hart
                                                  Esq</persName> as referees, I would esteem<lb/> it
                                        a particular favor if in conjunction or separately as
                                        may<lb/> best be deemed advisable, you would address a few
                                        lines to<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr. Jacob De La Motta</persName>, Parnass
                                                  <persName>K. K. Mick</persName><add>?</add>'
                                        Israel <placeName>Savanna, Ga</placeName><lb/> and furnish
                                        him with such information of the applicant as<lb/> you may
                                        deem justly merited.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. J. H. Bernal</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
